H0.text: Historically, what type of wood was used to make black piano keys. Rosewood

A4.text: Piano keys have often been made from ivory over the instrument's history

A5.text: Black keys were traditionally made of ebony, and the white keys were covered with strips of ivory.

A6.text: White keys were covered with strips of ivory.
